Post-Teleconsultation Functional Flow
🔷 1. Consultation Closure

Doctor:

Adds consultation notes
Prescribes medication (optional)
Defines follow-up date


System:

Marks session as “Completed”




🔷 2. Medical Record Update (EHR/FHIR)

System:

Converts notes → FHIR resources (Encounter, Observation, CarePlan updates)
Stores in FHIR system



✅ Ensures clinical record continuity

🔷 3. Care Plan Update / Creation

If care plan exists:

Updated with:

New activities
Follow-up task




If not:

New care plan may be created



✅ Enables ongoing care coordination

🔷 4. Follow-Up Appointment Workflow

System automatically:

Creates follow-up appointment (tentative or confirmed)
Or sends reminder to patient to book



✅ Ensures continuity of care

🔷 5. Notification Trigger

Notifications sent via ACS:

To Patient:

Consultation summary
Follow-up date reminder


To Care Coordinator:

New task / care update





✅ Keeps all stakeholders informed

🔷 6. Task Generation (Care Coordination)

Tasks created for:

Patient (e.g., medication adherence, tests)
Care Coordinator (e.g., monitoring follow-up)


Stored in Care Plan / Workflow engine

✅ Drives proactive care execution

🔷 7. Event Publishing (Event-Driven Flow)
Events triggered:

ConsultationCompletedEvent
CarePlanUpdatedEvent
FollowUpScheduledEvent

Consumed by:

Notification Service
Analytics
Monitoring

✅ Enables decoupled downstream processing

🔷 8. Alerts & Monitoring Setup

If critical findings:

Alert rules configured


System may:

Trigger alerts for abnormal conditions



✅ Supports risk-based monitoring

🔷 9. Analytics & Reporting

Data flows to:

Analytics service


Updates:

Patient history
KPIs (consultations, adherence)



✅ Enables insights & decision-making

🔷 10. Audit Logging

Logs captured:

Doctor actions
Record updates
Follow-up creation



✅ Ensures compliance & traceability
